   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide Psychiatric Medications in West Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will help finance essential medications for 14,000 residential patients with chronic mental illness and seizure disorders (epilepsy) in treatment at Association Saint Camille (ASC).  ASC is a comprehensive outpatient and residential treatment program in Benin, Togo and Ivory Coast.  Medication costs average $700,000 per year for 125,000 consultations.   ACS is unique in accepting all patients regardless of ability to pay. Patients are asked to pay $2.00 per month for medications.</narrative>
  </description>
